com.spartanlaboratories.engine.game

Class GameObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.spartanlaboratories.engine.structure.StructureObject
      • com.spartanlaboratories.engine.game.GameObject
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Aura, Buff, VisibleObject

    public abstract class GameObject
extends StructureObject
    One of the most basic of the engines object frameworks. Can be active or inactive, exists in the world, and can own other game objects.
    Since:
    Pre-A
    Author:
    Spartak

    • Field Detail

      • active

        public boolean active
        Determines whether or not this GameObject is active. If it is active then it will tick and draw, if it is not active then it will not. While this may vary between subclasses an object that is set to be inactive will most likely be deleted. Set to true on creation.

      • tick

        public boolean tick()
        Performs one update on the state of this game object. This method is called systematically by the engine and therefore it would be bad practice to call the method externally.
        Returns:
        whether or not this object is active
